description:
drh added on 2015-02-09 15:16:07:
All four of the following queries should return TRUE (1) according to the
COLLATE operator rules defined in the SQLite documentation 
(https://www.sqlite.org/datatype3.html#collation section 6.1).
SELECT 'abc'==('ABC'||'') COLLATE nocase;
SELECT 'abc'==('ABC'||'' COLLATE nocase);
SELECT 'abc'==('ABC'||('' COLLATE nocase));
SELECT 'abc'==('ABC'||upper('' COLLATE nocase));
However, in the 3.8.8.2 implementation (and probably all prior versions)
the final query returns FALSE (0).  Apparently the upper() function is
containing the COLLATE property and preventing it from propagating up to the
comparison operator.
